LABORATORY DATA
Hemoglobin 7.6.  White blood cell count 12.5.  Platelets 683.  Hematocrit 26.2.  MCV 61.6.  Sodium 136.  Potassium 3.4.  Glucose 99.  AST 22.  Total bili 0.5.  Creatinine-1.  BUN 14.  Chloride 101.  Bicarb 21.  Lipase 14.
ASSESSMENT/PLAN
#1 Sigmoid colon mass
Suspicious for colon cancer.  Hepatic lesions are also noted.  Colorectal Surgery has been contacted by our emergency room colleagues, and we will ask them to continue to follow for further evaluation and management.
#2 Bowel obstruction
Secondary to number one above, we will anchor NG for decompression, NPO except a few ice chips, aggressive IV fluid resuscitation.
#3 Bilateral hydronephrosis
Suspect due to BPH.  Will attempt catheter.  Check renal ultrasound.  Creatinine is stable.  Electrolytes are stable.
#4 Hypokalemia
Potassium has been added to the IV fluids.
#5 Microcytic anemia due to number one above.
In anticipation of procedures/surgery, will transfuse 2 units of packed red blood cells.  Risks and benefits discussed with Mr. Young, and he is in agreement.
#6 VTE prophylaxis
Mechanical for now given possibility of procedure and anemia.
#7 Code status
DNR/DNI.  This was discussed with Mr. Young.

